{
  "doc_id": "56679",
  "text": "Lipid infusion in lean, obese, and type 2 diabetic adults, a model of short-term elevation of FFA, results in peripheral IR and decreased peripheral glucose disposal [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] (13) [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . The FFA effect on peripheral IR is dose dependent and occurs at the level of insulin-stimulated glucose uptake, adversely affecting insulin signaling pathways [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] .",
